The Herald Conrad Mupesa Mashonaland West Bureau
Two police officers from Mhangura police station were nabbed by the Zimbabwe Anti-Corruption Commission for clearing stolen cattle in 2015. Constable Enifas Madzivanzira (36) and Sergeant Patricia Mashayamombe (42), who were denied bail on Tuesday when they appeared before Chinhoyi magistrate, Mr Tapiwa Banda, were arrested on March 20. They were both remanded in custody to April 6.